The Gemini Records collection for EPICS 3.14
--------------------------------------------

The geminiRec module provides the following records:
-  apply       Command Apply Record
-  cad         Command Action Directive Record
-  car         Command Action Response Record
-  cmdTimeout  Command Time Out Record
-  genSub      General Subroutine Record
-  lutin       Lookup Table Input Record
-  lutout      Lookup Table Output Record
-  sir         Status Information Record  
-  status      Status Record

The geminiRec module provides soft device support for following input/output records:
-  lutin
-  lutout
-  status

The geminiRec/geminRecApp/Db  directory contains: 
                 The capfast symbols for the various Gemini records.
                 The file "gemrec-edb.def" containing additional entries to
                      be added to the system edb.def file.
                 The file "gemrec-tdct.cfg" contianing additional entries to
                      be added to the system tdct.cfg file.

                 If the following hasn't already been done at your site:
                 (1) Copy the symbols capfast/*.sym to the relevant location.
                     - capfast: Probably $EPICS/extensions/src/edif/lib/sym
                     - tdct: Probably $(TDCT_INSTALL_LOCATION)/library/epics
                 (2) Add the lines in capfast/gemrec-edb.def to your edb.def file.
                     - capfast: Probably at $EPICS/extensions/src/edif/lib/edb.def
                     - tdct: Probably at $(TDCT_INSTALL_LOCATION)/edb.def
                 (3) If using TDCT, insert the lines in capfast/gem-tdct-cfg 
                     into your tdct.cfg file just before the [endcfg] directive.
                     - tdct.cfg is probably located at ~/.tdct/tdct.cfg

